config.script:
import time
	
	# Refresh user table binding and rotate refresh icon.
	self.view.refreshBinding('custom.Data')
	self.rotateIcon()

customMethods.name: rotateIcon
customMethods.script:
import time
	
	# Rotate icon 360 degrees.
	for degree in range(0,361, 10):
		self.props.style.transform = 'rotate(' + str(degree) + 'deg)'
		time.sleep(0.0278)

data.Description: LABEL BLANK 4X6 - ROLL LABEL BLANK 4X6 ADHESIVE

messageHandlers.script:
logger = system.util.getLogger('import_productcodes')
	
	try:
	    csvString = payload.get("csvString")
	    csvDict = payload.get("csvDS")
	    pyData = system.dataset.toPyDataSet(csvDict)
	    queryPath = "app/Schedule/addProductCode"
	
	    for row in pyData:
	        params = {
	            "productCode": row["ProductCode"],
	            "description": row["Description"],
	            "enabled": row["IsEnabled"],
	            "idealRunRate": row["IdealRunRate"],
	            "rateUoM": row["RateUnitOfMeasure"],
	            "perUnitCost": row["PerUnitCost"],
	            "instructions": row["Instructions"]
	        }
	
	        system.db.runNamedQuery(queryPath, params)
	        system.perspective.sendMessage("addedPC")
	        system.perspective.closePopup("ImportFile")
	
	except Exception as e:
	    errorParams = {
	        "ModalName": "ErrorModal",
	        "ErrorMessage": str(e),
	    }
	
	    system.perspective.openPopup("ErrorModal", "GlobalComponents/Modals/ErrorModal", errorParams)
	    logger.warn('There was an error: ' + str(e))
